        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 1:51PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 150 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
West Sand Lake, or near East Greenbush, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Albany, Troy, East Greenbush, Watervliet, Rensselaer, Nassau,
Menands, Stephentown, New Lebanon, Berlin, West Sand Lake,
Wyantskill, Averill Park, Wynantskill, North Greenbush, Sand Lake,
Poestenkill, East Nassau, South Troy, and Albia.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 90 between exits 10 and 6.
Interstate 787 between exits 1 and 7.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
